                    <comment id="12710620" author="john.wang@gmail.com" created="Tue, 19 May 2009 06:54:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;2.4.0 branch: IndexWriter.java, method: resolveExternalSegments, line 3072:&lt;br/&gt;
  final MergePolicy.OneMerge newMerge = new MergePolicy.OneMerge(segmentInfos.range(i, 1+i), info.getUseCompoundFile());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;info.getUseCompoundFile() seems to be wrong, this is on the src index, not the target index, should be getUseCompoundFile() instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12710680" author="mikemccand" created="Tue, 19 May 2009 10:42:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Good catch!  That&apos;s in the resolveExternalSegments method, which simply copies over (one for one) any segments from the source index that didn&apos;t &quot;need&quot; merging according to the merge policy.  Were there any other places in addIndexesNoOptimize where we don&apos;t preserve CFS properly?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yasuhiro/John, could you work up a unit test showing the problem, w/ patch showing that the test passes?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12718434" author="mikemccand" created="Thu, 11 Jun 2009 13:52:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the test case &amp;amp; committed.  Thanks Yasuhiro!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
